{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:psalms.93",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 93,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 93 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:1",
      "text": "The praise of a Song by David. Come, let us exult in the Lord; let us make a joyful noise to God our Saviour.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:2",
      "text": "Let us come before his presence with thanksgiving, and make a joyful noise to him with psalms.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:3",
      "text": "For the Lord is a great God, and a great king over all gods: for the Lord will not cast off his people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:4",
      "text": "For the ends of the earth are in his hands; and the heights of the mountains are his.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:5",
      "text": "For the sea is his, and he made it: and his hands formed the dry land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:6",
      "text": "Come, let us worship and fall down before him; and weep before the Lord that made us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:7",
      "text": "For he is our God; and we are the people of his pasture, and the sheep of his hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:8",
      "text": "✡ To-day, if ye will hear his voice, harden not your hearts, as in the provocation, according to the day of irritation in the wilderness:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:9",
      "text": "where your fathers tempted me, proved me, and saw my works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:10",
      "text": "Forty years was I grieved with this generation, and said, They do always err in their heart, and they have not known my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:11",
      "text": "So I sware in my wrath, They shall not enter into my rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:12",
      "text": "Blessed is the man whomsoever thou shalt chasten, O Lord, and shalt teach him out of thy law;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:13",
      "text": "to give him rest from evil days, until a pit be digged for the sinful one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:14",
      "text": "For the Lord will not cast off his people, neither will he forsake his inheritance;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:15",
      "text": "until righteousness return to judgment, and all the upright in heart shall follow it. Pause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:16",
      "text": "Who will rise up for me against the transgressors? or who will stand up with me against the workers of iniquity?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:17",
      "text": "If the Lord had not helped me, my soul had almost sojourned in Hades.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:18",
      "text": "If I said, My foot has been moved;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:19",
      "text": "thy mercy, O Lord, helped me. O Lord, according to the multitude of my griefs within my heart, thy consolations have soothed my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:20",
      "text": "Shall the throne of iniquity have fellowship with thee, which frames mischief by an ordinance?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:21",
      "text": "They will hunt for the soul of the righteous, and condemn innocent blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:22",
      "text": "But the Lord was my refuge; and my God the helper of my hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.93.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 93,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 93:23",
      "text": "And he will recompense to them their iniquity and their wickedness: the Lord our God shall utterly destroy them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
